               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0194THMR">May Raza Takla Hāymānot / THMR</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1881" notAfter="1889">King Yoḥannǝs (probably Yoḥannǝs IV,
                        r. 1872-89) is mentioned on <locus target="#30va">30va</locus>, 42a, 96ra.
                        Patriarch ʾabbā Qerǝllos and Metropolitan ʾabbā Ṗeṭros are mentioned on
                           <locus target="#42ra">42ra</locus>. Cyril V was the patriarch of
                        Alexandria in 1874-1927 and Ṗeṭros was the metropolitan of in Ethiopia
                        1881-1917.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Walatta Mikāʾel according to Additio 1. She
                     and her family members are also mentioned in the supplication formulas, often
                     written in a secondary hand in reddish-brown ink: Habta Śǝllāse (e.g., 16ra, 24ra, 24vb), Ḫāyla Māryām (16rb, 24rb, 24vb), Walda Māryām (23vb, 24va, 31ra), Walatta Mikāʾel (24rab, 24vb, 50rb, 71vab), Walatta Māryām (44rb, 90rb), Walatta Tǝnśāʾe (65vb, 78vb), Walatta Śǝllāse (67vb,
                     78rb), Lahǝyä Dǝngǝl (77rb, 78rb,
                     82vb).</provenance></history>
